-- в”Ђв”Ђ Cliniko в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Cliniko is cloud-based practice management software for allied health clinics, handling appointment scheduling, patient records, clinical notes, telehealth, and billing in one system.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$45/month (solo practitioner)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2011, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$60+ employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Melbourne, Australia$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Cliniko Review: Features, Pricing & Plans (2026)$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Cliniko is practice management software for allied health clinics with scheduling, patient records, telehealth, and billing. See pricing by practitioner count and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Cliniko is cloud-based practice management software for allied health practitioners вЂ” including physiotherapists, chiropractors, psychologists, podiatrists, and similar clinics вЂ” founded in 2011 (with the company noting pricing has stayed on the same structure since June that year) by co-founders Joel Friedlaender and Liora Dafner-Beach in Melbourne, Australia, where it remains headquartered and privately, wholly owned by its original founders. The company employs roughly 60 people distributed globally. Cliniko's product covers the operational core of running a clinic: appointment scheduling with an online patient booking widget, patient records and configurable clinical note templates, treatment notes, telehealth video consultations, invoicing and payment processing, and integrated SMS/email appointment reminders. Rather than segmenting features behind multiple pricing tiers, Cliniko uses a single-tier, practitioner-count-based pricing model: every subscriber gets the full feature set, unlimited admin/reception users, unlimited patient records, and unlimited file storage, with the monthly price scaling purely by how many practitioners are on the account. As of the current published pricing, a solo practitioner pays $45/month, 2-5 practitioners pay $95/month, 6-8 practitioners pay $145/month, 9-12 practitioners pay $195/month, 13-25 practitioners pay $295/month, and clinics with 26-200 practitioners pay $395/month (in the currency of the subscribing region вЂ” Cliniko publishes pricing in AUD, USD, GBP, and EUR depending on the customer's location). Cliniko offers a 30-day free trial that requires no credit card, and annual billing includes one additional free month compared to paying monthly. Optional add-on costs include SMS messaging at roughly 10 cents per message via a pre-paid credit system, and some third-party integrations may carry separate fees from those providers. Cliniko donates roughly 2% of subscription revenue to charity as a stated company practice. The platform is used by solo practitioners up through larger multi-location allied health groups, and it is positioned specifically for allied health rather than for general medical practices, dental clinics, or hospital systems вЂ” its feature set (treatment notes, outcome measures, health fund claiming in supported regions) reflects that focus. Because Cliniko's pricing has intentionally remained simple and flat-feature since its early years, prospective buyers do not need to compare feature matrices across tiers the way they would with most SaaS products вЂ” the primary purchasing decision is simply how many practitioners will use the account.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'd221b5a0-51a9-4fa0-9bbd-a8dd91499f83';

