-- в”Ђв”Ђ Clio в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Clio is cloud-based legal practice management software for law firms, covering time tracking, billing, trust accounting, client intake, and document management.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$49/user/month (EasyStart, billed annually)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2007, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$2,000+ employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Burnaby, British Columbia, Canada$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Clio Review: Features, Pricing & Plans (2026)$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Clio is cloud-based legal practice management software with billing, trust accounting, and client intake. Compare EasyStart, Essentials, Advanced, and Complete plans.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Clio, operated by Themis Solutions Inc., is cloud-based legal practice management software founded in 2007 by Jack Newton and Rian Gauvreau. The company is headquartered in Burnaby, British Columbia, Canada, and has grown into a large legal technology employer with more than 2,000 employees across offices including Toronto, Calgary, London, Manchester, Dublin, Sydney, Barcelona, and BogotГЎ; Clio has been recognized as one of Canada's Top 100 Employers. The company reports serving more than 400,000 legal professionals across over 130 countries, making it one of the most widely adopted practice management platforms in the legal industry. Clio's core product, Clio Manage, centralizes the day-to-day operations of running a law firm: client and matter management, calendaring and court-date tracking, time and expense tracking, document management and templates, e-signatures, and billing, invoicing, and trust (IOLTA) accounting that follows jurisdiction-specific compliance rules. The company also sells companion products, including Clio Grow for client intake and lead management, and has invested in AI features (marketed under the Clio Duo/AI drafting umbrella) for drafting and summarizing legal documents in its higher tiers. Clio Manage is sold in four tiers billed per user per month on an annual basis: EasyStart at $49/user/month covering basic time tracking, billing, and trust accounting for solo practitioners; Essentials at $89/user/month, described as the firm's most popular tier, adding fuller practice management workflows; Advanced at $119/user/month, aimed at established small-to-mid-size firms and adding unlimited e-signatures, advanced reporting, and priority support; and Complete at $149/user/month, the top tier, bundling client intake automation and AI drafting capabilities alongside full practice management. Monthly (non-annual) billing typically costs $10-20 more per user per month than the listed annual rates. Firms often incur additional costs beyond the base subscription, such as Clio Payments processing fees (around 2.95% plus $0.20 per transaction) and optional integrations like QuickBooks Online. Clio is available as a web application with iOS and Android mobile apps, and it integrates with widely used legal and accounting tools. It targets law firms of essentially any size, from solo attorneys on EasyStart up to larger multi-partner firms on Advanced or Complete that need e-signatures, advanced reporting, and AI-assisted drafting. Because Clio bundles trust accounting compliance features directly into its billing module, it is particularly relevant to firms in jurisdictions with strict client-fund handling rules, which is a key differentiator versus general-purpose practice or project management software not built for legal-specific compliance.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '4a9597db-c7eb-4543-a969-70c7a5b25c4e';

