-- в”Ђв”Ђ Clockify в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Clockify is a time-tracking and timesheet platform from CAKE.com with reporting, invoicing, and 100+ integrations, offering a free plan for small teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (paid plans from $3.99/user/month billed annually)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2017, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$200+ employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Palo Alto, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Russian$q$, $q$Serbian$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Clockify Review: Features, Pricing & Plans (2026)$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Clockify is a time-tracking app with timesheets, reporting, and invoicing. Compare Free, Basic, Standard, Pro, and Enterprise plans, features, and pricing.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Clockify is a time-tracking and timesheet platform launched in 2017 by the company now branded CAKE.com Inc. (previously known as COING), headquartered at 2100 Geng Road in Palo Alto, California, with a privately held team of over 200 employees. Clockify was built around a simple pitch вЂ” offer time tracking to unlimited users for free вЂ” and it grew into the most widely used product in what is now the CAKE.com productivity suite, which also includes Pumble (team chat) and Plaky (project management). As of the current pricing structure, Clockify's Free plan is capped at 5 users (a change introduced in April 2026; the plan previously supported unlimited users on the free tier) and includes unlimited time tracking, timers, manual time entry, timesheets, an auto-tracker, calendar view, mobile/desktop apps, basic reporting, and team activity views, but excludes invoicing, billable rates, project budgets, timesheet approvals, GPS tracking, and audit logs. Paid tiers scale up from there: Basic at $3.99/user/month (annual) or $4.99 (monthly) adds a kiosk mode, the ability to add time for others, hidden time/pages, required fields, bulk editing, break tracking, time estimates, and import tools; Standard at $5.49/user/month (annual) or $6.99 (monthly) adds time-off tracking, invoicing and recurring invoices, timesheet approval workflows, timesheet locking, attendance/overtime tracking, a manager role, task-level billing rates, and QuickBooks integration; Pro at $7.99/user/month (annual) or $9.99 (monthly) adds scheduling, forecasting, expense tracking, labor cost and profit analysis, budgets and estimates, custom fields, multi-currency support, GPS tracking, screenshots, and email reports; and Enterprise at $11.99/user/month (annual) or $14.99 (monthly) adds single sign-on (SSO), a custom subdomain, SCIM provisioning, control accounts, and an audit log. CAKE.com also sells a bundled plan combining Enterprise-tier Clockify with Pumble and Plaky at $12.99/user/month (annual) or $15.99 (monthly), marketed as saving roughly 53% versus subscribing to the three products separately. Clockify supports 90+ third-party integrations spanning project management and communication tools, letting teams embed time tracking into existing workflows rather than switching context. The product is available as a web app plus native desktop apps for macOS, Windows, and Linux, and mobile apps for iOS and Android. Clockify is aimed at freelancers and very small teams on the free tier, growing agencies and consultancies needing invoicing and approvals on Standard, and larger organizations needing budgeting, forecasting, and enterprise security controls (SSO, SCIM, audit logs) on Pro and Enterprise.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '727ce456-3ada-4396-a467-30164d11f40e';

